write a query that:

First identifies "large devices" (devices with width greater than 200)
Then calculates the average score for these large devices. Call this column as average_score
Use the WITH clause to solve this problem.

With large_devices AS (
    Select width, device_id
    From devices_specs
    Where width > 200
)
Select AVG(ds.score) AS average_score 
From devices_score AS ds
Join large_devices AS ld 
ON ld.device_id = ds.device_id  

A device's quality is measured by (width/height)*num_features.
We want to find all of the overrated devices. Fetch all of the devices where the device's opinion is greater than the average quality and the device's score is less than the average quality. Return only the device_id.
To solve it, use the WITH clause to create a subquery that calculates the average quality and reuse it in the main query.

WITH overrated_devices AS (
    Select AVG((width/height)*num_features) AS avg_quality 
    From devices_specs
)
Select ds.device_id
From devices_specs AS ds
JOIN devices_score ds_score 
ON ds.device_id = ds_score.device_id
WHERE ds.opinion > (SELECT avg_quality FROM overrated_devices)
  AND ds_score.score < (SELECT avg_quality FROM overrated_devices);

